A man died and three others were injured yesterday morning, (Monday, 22 May), when a light motor vehicle and taxi collided at the Long Market and Retief Road intersection in Pietermaritzburg CBD.ER24 paramedics, with other services, arrived at the scene at about 6.30am. Upon arrival, paramedics found a taxi lying on its side towards the pavement. A light motor vehicle had come to a stop a short distance away, said Russel Meiring, ER24 spokesperson. Paramedics found the body of a man, lying near his light motor vehicle. He had apparently been pulled from the vehicle by a member of the public. The man was assessed and found to have sustained numerous injuries and showed no signs of life. Unfortunately, nothing could be done for the man and he was declared dead. Three other men, who were in the taxi at the time of the accident, sustained minor injuries. Patients were treated at the scene and then taken to hospital. Police are investigating the cause of the accident.